            . I am shopman to Messrs Hill and Parkinson. On the <rs id="t18070916-135-cd722" type="crimeDate">18th of June</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070916-135-off721 t18070916-135-cd722"></join> last, the prisoner came into the shop, and asked for two dozen o wax candles; he said he had not got any order; I told him Mr. Wyat requested that he should not have the goods without the order; he said that Mr. Wyat and his clerk were in the warehouse, they desired him to make all the haste they could for the candles for the carriage was waiting at the door for them; under this circumstance, I let him have them. I wrote a bill out in Mr. Wyat's name and gave him the bill.</p>
               <p>
            
